title: Out of the Hive
description: Helicopter pilot Ed, electronics expert Ros Henderson and government agent Nick Beckett find themselves working together in an attempt to prevent the theft of a powerful satellite device from a government agency.

title: Assassins Inc.
description: When Ed, Ros and Beckett set out on a mission to bring down hi-tech weapons dealer Irene Campbell, she targets the team with her latest and most lethal technology.

title: All Under Control
description: When a passenger aircraft is hijacked by remote control, the Gizmos team is called in to investigate the plane's state-of-the-art navigation system.

title: Down Among the Dead Men
description: Hired to investigate the link between the theft of ship components and the former employee of a large city bank, the Gizmos team encounter theft, murder, and a bank heist by submarine.

title: Shotgun Wedding
description: When the team's plan to protect Italian politician Anna Fabrizi from a lethal assassin goes horribly wrong, Ed is forced to go undercover and must make an impossible decision - kill Anna Fabrizi or die.

title: Stealth
description: When Gizmos are hired to provide security for the launch of a new sports car, they instead become caught up in the theft of a prototype nuclear-powered stealth tank, which could destroy the city if not recovered.

title: Manna from Heaven
description: Phodex is a revolutionary type of food which could end world famine. When an attempt is made to steal samples, Gizmos are called in to investigate - and they discover that Phodex holds a deadly secret.

title: Hot Metal
description: When a new type of metal is discovered to have explosive properties, Gizmos are brought in to prevent it's theft by a mercenary who has developed a way to silence explosions.

title: A Sporting Chance
description: Gizmos stumble across the sinister plans of mercenary Colonel Easterhaus when they investigate the collapse of several athletes at a sports institution.

title: Pulse
description: Whilst investigating the disappearance of several company executives, Ed, Ros and Beckett stumble on to a plan to destroy the economic centers of London and Geneva, devised by a criminal mastermind.

title: What Goes Up...
description: Ed goes undercover on a space program to oversee the deployment of a new satellite. But as the seconds tick down to the launch, a saboteur prepares to strike.

title: ...Must Come Down
description: Whilst Ed is stranded aboard the crippled shuttle, Ros and Beckett attempt to unmask the saboteur within Ground Control. Meanwhile, a more deadly enemy resurfaces.

title: Bugged Wheat
description: The team comes up against a pesticide company's scheme to spread worldwide famine, using genetically engineered insects infected with a deadly micro-virus.

title: Whirling Dervish
description: When a consortium of airlines plans to use a stealth plane to bring down a rival passenger airline, Ed goes undercover as a fighter pilot. Meanwhile, the team realize that someone is manipulating them.

title: Blackout
description: A guided tour of a hi-tech nuclear power station turns into a hostage crisis for Ros when the building is stormed by eco-terrorists. However, the situation is not what it seems.

title: Gold Rush
description: The Monetary Commission recruits the team when a microbe is released into their gold vault which will literally eat their gold reserves. Whilst Ros goes after the antidote, Ed becomes trapped in the vault as lethal security countermeasures are activated.

title: The Bureau of Weapons
description: The Gizmos team race to stop Jean-Daniel after he unleashes an artificial intelligence across the Internet - leading Ros to make a terrible sacrifice.

title: A Cage for Satan
description: As Jean-Daniel puts the final stages of his master-plan into action, Ed and Beckett must prevent Ros from unwittingly activating the deadly computer virus stored within her mind.
